<p>This tab lists the domains to which the message has been sent. The domain is is the part of the email address after the '@' character.</p><table><tr><td>Heading</td><td>This shows the message ID and subject, and the list or lists to which the message has been sent.</td></tr><tr><td>Download</td><td>The fields displayed can be downloaded as a CSV file.</td></tr><tr><td>Domain</td><td>The domain.</td></tr><tr><td>Sent</td><td>The number of users in the domain who were sent the message.</td></tr><tr><td>Opened</td><td>The number of users in the domain who have opened the message.</td></tr><tr><td>Clicked</td><td>The number of users in the domain who have clicked at least one link in the message.</td></tr></table>